commit_list.message: Add setup_requires caveat to repeatability section.

Make stopwatch work with test methods.

Prior to this commit, test methods are always run, even if they are
slower than the "--faster-than" threshold.

The problem was, stopTest put the qualified name of the test class in
the dontrun dict, instead of the qualified name of the *method*.

To fix this, we use the id() method of test to get the qualified name,
just as xunit, a built-in plugin to nose, does.

Fix completion of "sysd systemctl" and don't run "service". (#1)

* Don't run 'service' if you can't find systemctl.

The two programs aren't interchangeable.

Plus, on Ubuntu/Debian systems, service is in /usr/sbin.

* Add systemctl to list of subcommands.

As far as I can tell, it was just an oversight that it has been
omitted.
